Companion (bottom-screen barter) — export + control bridge for the native
TradeWindow (GM_Barter). Mirrors companion-dialogue-export.patch:

Outbound (COMPANION_BARTER_*, streamed one small line each for 4096-byte flush
safety): OPEN{vendor,vendorGold,playerGold} → ITEM{side,id,sid,name,count,value,
cat,icon,worn}* (vendor items then player items; value = the merchant's actual
per-unit barter price via getBarterOffer, NOT base value) → END; then a running
OFFER{merchantOffer,balance,extraGold,vendorGold,playerGold} after every change
(balance = the authoritative net the player is offering); OFFER_ACCEPTED /
OFFER_REJECTED{reason} on an offer; CLOSED on close. Also re-emits the existing
COMPANION_DIALOGUE_DISPOSITION prefix from TradeWindow::onFrame, because
DialogueWindow::onFrame (the normal emit site) does NOT run while GM_Barter is
the top mode, so the bottom-screen disposition bar would otherwise freeze.

Inbound: a file-static gCompanionTradeWindow (set in the ctor) plus five
extern "C" bridges — companionBarterBorrow/Return/SetGold/Offer/Cancel — let
drainCompanionCommands drive the offer from CMP:barter_* commands. Items are
matched by serialized RefId. gCompanionExtraGold holds the player's manual gold
offset so it survives item changes (updateOffer only shifts the balance by the
merchant-offer delta). companionOffer() mirrors onOfferButtonClicked but reports
each rejection reason to the bottom screen instead of a native messageBox.

Each bridge no-ops unless containsMode(GM_Barter) (stale-window guard).
